printer_notes.3.0.0: Do not remove the following keywords! These keywords are used in the "compatible printer" condition of the print and filament profiles to link the particular print and filament profiles to this printer profile.\nPRINTER_VENDOR_BIBO\nPRINTER_MODEL_BIBO2

deretract_speed.3.0.0: 0,0 # Setting this value to 0 uses the retract speed

end_gcode.3.0.0:
;BIBO End GCode
M107 ; turn fans off
G91 ; Relative positioning
G1 Z1 F100
M140 S0    ; Disable heated bed
M104 T0 S0 ; extruder T0 heater off
M104 T1 S0 ; extruder T1 heater off
G1 Z+0.5 X-20 Y-20 F300 ; move Z down then move print head a bit out of the way
G28 X0 Y0 ; move X/Y to min endstops, so the head is out of the way
G90    ; Absolute positioning
G92 E0.0 ; Reset extruder position
M84    ; Turn steppers off
M117 BIBO Print complete ; Put print complete message on screen

start_gcode.3.0.0:
;Start code PrusaSlicer BIBO 2 printers
G21  ; set units to metric
G90  ; absolute positioning
M107 ; start with the fan off
M190 S{max(first_layer_bed_temperature[0] - 5, first_layer_bed_temperature[1] - 5)} ; wait for bed temp
M140 S{max(first_layer_bed_temperature[0], first_layer_bed_temperature[1])}  ; continue bed heating to full temp while other things are happening
M104 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T0; set 1st nozzle heater to first layer temperature
M104 S{first_layer_temperature[1]} T1; set 2nd nozzle heater to first layer temperature
M109 S{first_layer_temperature[0]} T0; wait for 1st nozzle heat to first layer temperature
M109 S{first_layer_temperature[1]} T1; wait for 2nd nozzle heat to first layer temperature
T0   ; Start at T0 to avoid extruder nozzle offset issues
G28 X0 Y0      ; move X/Y to min endstops
G28 Z0         ; move Z to min endstops
G1 Z2.0 F400   ; move the platform down 2mm
G92 E0.0       ; reset extruder
G1 Y0 F1200 E0 ; move Y to min endstop and extrude 0 filament
T[initial_tool]; switch to initial tool position
G92 E0.0       ; reset extruder and zero the current extruder coordinate before printing
M117 BIBO now Printing... ; Put now printing message on screen
